      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HIGH TEMPO (2) faces the starter for the first time. By Ride High and hails from the Emma Stewart stable. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Trial winner who looks above average. Well-placed to score at his first appearance. ALL OVER IT (8) scored two runs back then registered an effortless win last time out, scoring by 12 metres over 2190m at Shepparton. Can settle just behind them and wait on the sprint lane. Finds a nice race and will take plenty of beating once more. MASTER LOUEY (4) has been hard to fault of late, adding to the winning tally last start with success over 1609m at Cranbourne. No reason the run cannot continue. Looks a gap to the others with LIKE NO OTHER (3) next best.",
